The current price of ADA is $1.43. ADA has maintained a price > $1 since early February (4 months) and, while the price has been dropping since its ATH, is not dropping that quickly. Therefore, assuming a stable rate of deprecation, the price will stay above $1 until July. On-top of this Cardano is rolling out smart contracts which will increase the number of users and should result in an increase of price. I don't believe the price will increase drastically to $2.50 (it's too tightly coupled to Bitcoin) but this may help slow down or reverse the ongoing price drop.

When I made my last forecast, the price was $1.21, now it's $2.04. I still feel pretty confident about the $1.00 to $2.50 range, but now it seems there is a greater likelihood of it being on the high side than the low side. Of course, all the crypto is extremely volatile, so hard to say what will happen. It could double or halve between now and then. But, notably, halving still keeps it in the $1.00 to $2.50 range. I am flipping my upside and downside and throwing in a little extra to the upside. There is no particularly rigorous reason.
